This article is a memorandum issued by President Barack Obama in January 2013. The memorandum states that the President has determined it is important to provide assistance for unexpected urgent refugee and migration needs relating to Syria. The President authorizes an amount not to exceed $15 million from the United States Emergency Refugee and Migration Assistance Fund for this purpose. The assistance may include contributions to international, governmental, and nongovernmental organizations, as well as payment of administrative expenses of the Bureau of Population, Refugees, and Migration of the Department of State. The Secretary of State is instructed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.